We found you lying in the street last night,
just by our gate.

51:13.613 --> 51:14.978
Rough night?

51:15.114 --> 51:20.780
We thought to take you home,
but you had no keys. No wallet either.

51:20.912 --> 51:24.450
— Coffee?
— Uh...

51:27.835 --> 51:29.746
You guys brought me in?

51:29.879 --> 51:32.370
We're your neighbors.

51:48.564 --> 51:49.849
Yes, sir?

51:51.025 --> 51:55.610
What's the most trombone I can buy...
for that?

51:59.492 --> 52:01.357
The Conn, probably.

52:01.494 --> 52:04.327
Now is it for you or for a kid taking lessons?

52:04.455 --> 52:06.537
— Because you could rent.
- Nah.

52:06.666 --> 52:09.703
l have a hell of a horn right now, me.

52:09.836 --> 52:14.375
This is for a friend who lost his in the storm.

52:14.507 --> 52:16.463
Nah.

52:18.177 --> 52:21.419
What the fu...
Let me see that one right there.

52:39.365 --> 52:40.866
What does that say, bro?

52:41.784 --> 52:44.901
— "AB. '79."
- Mm-hm.

52:49.125 --> 52:51.241
"A.B." mother...

52:54.339 --> 52:56.421
You know I'm not picking that up.

52:56.549 --> 52:58.915
I'm taking this to the US Attorney's office.

52:59.052 --> 53:00.917
Those guys not only beat my client down,

53:01.054 --> 53:03.420
they took his property
to Carondelet Street for pawn.

53:03.556 --> 53:08.266
Never mind dirty.
I expect dirty in this town, but that's just stupid.

53:08.394 --> 53:10.225
Like they want to get caught.

53:11.481 --> 53:14.063
Toni, between the guys
who quit during the storm

53:14.192 --> 53:18.356
and the guys that we fired aftenNards,
I'm at 60% in this district.

53:18.488 --> 53:22.276
And the guys who are still on the job,
they got no homes, no money.

53:22.408 --> 53:25.024
Their families are living out of town,
most of them.

53:25.161 --> 53:27.777
Guys drinking, guys who won't
get out of their cars to work.

53:27.914 --> 53:30.872
Never mind some of them worked
two weeks straight after the storm.

53:31.000 --> 53:34.584
They were fucking heroes. Now they know
what the rest of the world thinks.

53:34.712 --> 53:37.749
They've seen the New Orleans police
on the news for looting,

53:37.882 --> 53:41.090
for beating on people,
for the Danziger Bridge Shootings.

53:41.219 --> 53:43.926
The guys who did this, it's...

53:45.515 --> 53:47.551
It's like a cry for help.

53:49.644 --> 53:51.680
It's all coming back, isn't it?

53:52.480 --> 53:54.596
For a moment the storm took it away.

53:54.732 --> 53:57.974
No dope, no guns. No guns, no bodies.

53:58.111 --> 54:00.477
— You know Cosgrove?
—Mm?

54:00.613 --> 54:03.150
