new circumstances.

56:17.583 --> 56:20.199
- Lots to talk about.
— You sound thrilled.

56:20.336 --> 56:21.701
Good news comes by phone.

56:21.837 --> 56:24.704
When a New York literary agent
travels 1,000 miles,

56:24.840 --> 56:27.923
that means the publisher
wants their advance returned.

56:28.052 --> 56:30.964
l'm six years late on this novel.

56:31.097 --> 56:34.260
Random House is fed the fuck up
and wants their money back.

56:34.392 --> 56:36.929
— She said that?
— With the money we spent on the new roof

56:37.061 --> 56:40.098
and lowering our mortgage, guess what,
I got nothing to give 'em.

56:40.231 --> 56:41.892
- Creighton.
— What, Toni?

56:42.024 --> 56:43.855
What?

56:43.985 --> 56:45.646
(Laughing)

56:45.778 --> 56:48.485
That fuckin' agent's gonna ruin Mardi Gras!

56:48.614 --> 56:50.775
(Sighs)

57:05.298 --> 57:06.663
Sorry, bro.

57:06.799 --> 57:09.461
See you around, OK?
